The first step is create a folder "DEBIAN" in "/home/username/brisa-2.0/libbrisa-2.0-dev",and the file: 

"control" whose content is 

Source: libbrisa-2.0-dev
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Camilo Campos <zeromaisum@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5.0.38), libqt4-dev
Standards-Version: 3.8.2
Package: libbrisa-2.0-dev
Architecture: all
Section: devel
Depends: libqt4-dev
version:2.0
Description: The package will install the headers and the compiled files of the BRisa framework



The second step is to create the tree of folders "/home/username/brisa-2.0/libbrisa-2.0-dev/usr/include/BRisa", where you will put the .h and the compiled files of the BRisa framework.

The third step is to create the tree of folders "/home/username/brisa-2.0/libbrisa-2.0-dev/opt/qtsdk-2010.05/qt/mkspecs/features, where you will put the brisa.prf file.

The last step is go to the shell change the directory to "/home/username/brisa-2.0/libbrisa-2.0-dev" and type "dpkg -b libbrisa-2.0-dev" then the package libbrisa-2.0-dev.deb will be created.


* You have to use the qmake in the /opt/qtsdk-2010.05/qt/bin/qmake *

